    <h3>Paraguan&aacute; Refining Center (CRP)</h3>
    <p>
      The Centro de Refinaci&oacute;n Paraguan&aacute; &mdash; comprising the Amuay and
      Cardón refineries on the Paraguaná Peninsula &mdash; is one of the largest
      refining complexes in the world by nameplate capacity (955,000&nbsp;bpd). At
      peak performance in the late 1990s, CRP processed a mix of Venezuelan crude
      grades for export to the US Gulf Coast and Caribbean markets.
    </p>
    <p>
      As of early 2026, CRP is estimated to be processing ~280,000&ndash;300,000&nbsp;bpd,
      constrained by mechanical failures, a lack of spare parts, and periodic
      unplanned shutdowns. The Rodriguez government has prioritized CRP rehabilitation
      in its first 100-day economic plan.
    </p>

